        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 6:07PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 607 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hueco Tanks, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Far East El Paso, Hueco Tanks, Hueco Mountain Estates, Homestead
Meadows, and Butterfield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
